  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "The night before you intend to eat, pop your chickpeas in a bowl and cover them with water. Leave to soak for at least 10 hours."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat your oven to 200°C."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Cut your squash in half lengthways. Roast it in the oven for 45 mins until caramelised and tender."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pickle your chillies. Add your apple cider vinegar, 200ml water, sugar and a pinch of salt to a heatproof jug, then heat in a microwave until steaming."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Finely slice your green chillies, then pop them in a bowl. Pour your hot cider vinegar mix over the top, then leave them to pickle."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Make your kofte. Roughly chop your chillies and parsley. Grate your halloumi."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add your chickpeas to a food processor and pulse to break up slightly. Add the flesh from your butternut squash, chillies, fresh parsley, breadcrumbs, ground cumin, ground coriander, sumac and ½ tsp of salt. Blitz until it comes together in a paste."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add your halloumi and mix to combine."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Roll your mixture into balls, then pop in the fridge to chill for 15 mins."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Make your chopped salad. Finely dice your red onion. Dice your tomatoes and cucumber."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add your red onion to a bowl along with your lemon juice and a pinch of salt. Scrunch up with your hands to lightly pickle. Add your diced tomato, cucumber, a small handful of chopped parsley and your sumac."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat a generous glug of olive in a large frying pan. Once hot, add your kofte and fry for a few mins on each side until deeply golden and crisp."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add your butter to a heatproof dish and grate in your garlic. Microwave until the butter is just melted."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Warm your naan in the oven for a few mins."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Assembly time. Brush your naan with garlic butter, then dollop on a little yoghurt. Sprinkle with your chopped salad, then add a few kofte on top. Scatter with pickled chillies and a pinch of sumac, then serve."
    }
  ],
